Michel Richard Delalande Lalande December 1657 June 1726 was French Baroque composer and organist who was the service King Louis XIV was one the most important composers grands motets also wrote orchestral suites known Simphonies pour les Soupers Roy and ballets Born Paris was contemporary JeanBaptiste Lully and Franois Couperin Delalande taught music the daughters Louis XIV France and was director the French chapel royal from 1714 until his death Versailles 1726 Delalande was arguably the greatest composer French grands motets type sacred work that was more pleasing Louis XIV because its pomp and grandeur written for soloists choir and comparatively large orchestra According tradition Louis XIV organized contest between composers giving them the same sacred text and time compose the musical setting alone was the judge Delalande was one four winners assigned compose sacred music for each quarter the year the other composers being Coupillet Collasse and Minoret Delalandes was the most important quarter the year because the Christmas holiday Later had full responsibility for the church music for the complete year his death since left mass his own the 1656 requiem the Dukes Lorraine Charles dHelfer was sung Delalande left many versions his works His earlier versions show adherence French Baroque style but the later revisions incorporate more Italian melismatic lines and greater attention polyphonic counterpoint Also least four collections his works exist each displaying different looks composers work viewed the people who assembled each collection Scholarship Delalandes work was for many years hindered because inconsistencies the spelling his last name Lalande Lalande Lande Lande and others The family wrote the name Delalande Finally 2006 the definitive Thematic Catalogue the Works MichelRichard Lalande 16571726 noted British musicologist Lionel Sawkins came out which runs 752 pages containing over 3000 music examples and details performing requirements and all source materials well with comprehensive indexes and thematic locators Vocal InstrumentalLalande was expert organist and harpsichordist and yet has left not single note keyboard music 